claudioillanes wrote:
&gt; 
&gt; Hi all,
&gt; 
&gt; I am new to JUnit and I&#39;ve trying to combine a sequence of
&gt; testSuites. In one of my testXXX methods, I&#39;ve tried to create a
&gt; TestSuite() (with a listing of  suite.addTest(new TestSuite
&gt; (XXX.class)) ) and I want this testSuite to run its set of tests
&gt; before this particular testXXX method completes. What I&#39;ve tried is:
&gt; 
&gt; TestSuite packageSuite = new TestSuite();
&gt; packageSuite.addTest( OtherFile.suite() );
&gt; packageSuite.runTest(packageSuite, new TestResult());
&gt; 
&gt; Is this right?

No.

You appear to want to execute tests in a particular sequence; is that 
correct? If so, simply add them in the desired sequence.

public static Test suite() {
     TestSuite packageSuite = new TestSuite();
     packageSuite.addTest( OtherFile.suite() );
     packageSuite.addTest( new MyTestCase(&quot;testMethod&quot;) );
     ...
     return packageSuite;
}

JUnit will do the rest.

Do not try to create suites at run time. Create the suite first, then 
let JUnit run it.
